This paper deals with the problem of clustering spreadsheets based on their version information, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed algorithm, SpreadCluster, uses machine learning techniques to identify common features in spreadsheets and group them accordingly, which involves data mining and clustering (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing approaches and proposes a new method for recovering version information, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper emphasizes the importance of spreadsheet understanding and maintenance for end-users, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
